title: Indian Summer

This 1971 album from Coventry&#039;s very own Indian Summer is an absolute neglected classic of the era.
Bob Jackson&#039;s passionate yet subtle vocals and authentic trademark keyboards are standouts of this &#039;progressive&#039;, if you have to call it that, album. Loud and &#039;heavy&#039; at times, yet eerie and sensitive at other points.

Wonderful album that has it all.
